reviewText: I love what Schnabel has done with this not-quite-accurate account of J.M. Basquiat's life. It is so visually stunning, and the music seems to come straight from my own cd collection. I had this on vhs and now have it on dvd. A great film. Bravo, to a contemporary master!
A film to watch again and again, truly a work of art about an amazing artist.
...especially if you're an artist! Very interesting look at the artists' life! I was not at all familiar with him, but I was familiar with the era, so it had a lot of relevance!
